Orientation
Identification. The country is named after Captain James Cook, who landed there in 1773.
Location and Geography. The Cook Isâ€¦ </span> </span> </span> </a> <a href="https://www.encyclopedia.com/places/latin-america-and-caribbean/caribbean-political-geography/Montserrat" class="bib__link bib__link--5 bib__link--image"> <span class="bib__image" style="background-image: url('https://www.encyclopedia.com/sites/default/files/styles/slide_thumb/public/5/2800717.jpg?itok=gn1P4q7A')"></span> <span class="bib__info"> <span class="bib__title"> <span class="bib__name">Montserrat</span> </span> <span class="bib__properties"><span class="bib__recency">,</span></span> <span class="bib__preview"> <span class="bib__description"> Montserrat
Culture Name
Montserratian
Orientation
Identification. Before 1995, this pear-shaped island had a population of about ten thousand and wasâ€¦ </span> </span> </span> </a> <a href="https://www.encyclopedia.com/places/united-states-and-canada/us-political-geography/united-states-virgin-islands" class="bib__link bib__link--6 bib__link--image"> <span class="bib__image" style="background-image: url('https://www.encyclopedia.com/sites/default/files/styles/slide_thumb/public/7/5710152.jpg?itok=JrROoEmP')"></span> <span class="bib__info"> <span class="bib__title"> <span class="bib__name">United States Virgin Islands</span> </span> <span class="bib__properties"><span class="bib__recency">,</span></span> <span class="bib__preview"> <span class="bib__description"> At a Glance
Size: 136 sq. mi. (352 sq km)
Population: 122,211
Electoral votes: 0
U.S. Representatives: 1 (nonvoting)
